; PaideiaOS IPC Phase-1 Smoke Test: Kernel Logging
; P3-011f: Test kernel audit log channel (producer: kernel, consumer: log writer)
; Design reference: design/ipc/phase1-api.md §4

module IpcSmokeKernelLog

; Test: Simulate kernel audit log usage pattern

; Constants
AUDIT_CHANNEL_CAPACITY = 32      ; Audit log use case
AUDIT_SLOT_SIZE = 256
AUDIT_MESSAGE_COUNT = 10

; Expected outcomes:
; 1. ipc_create_channel(32, 256) simulates audit log channel creation
; 2. Loop: producer enqueues 10 audit event messages
;    - Each message is a structured audit entry (constant format for testing)
;    - Enqueue succeeds (capacity sufficient)
; 3. Consumer (log writer) dequeues all 10 messages in order
;    - Dequeue succeeds and returns message bytes
;    - FIFO order is preserved
; 4. Dequeue on empty channel returns DEQUEUE_EMPTY
; 5. Channel remains live for subsequent audit events

; Real-world pattern:
; Kernel audit subsystem enqueues events (e.g., syscall entry/exit, permission denials).
; A dedicated log writer thread or task dequeues and writes to persistent storage.
; The bounded buffer (32 slots) provides backpressure; if producer is faster than
; consumer, enqueue returns FULL and caller retries or logs locally.

; STUB: Constants and test outline only
; Runtime: Deferred to paideia-as Phase 7+

end module
